In my short time here on earth, I've noticed that the single most unlikely way to ever win an office pool based on March Madness brackets is to use logic or probabilities. The winners generally use things like "Who has prettier uniforms?" or other such nonsense to pick winners.This year, our free office pool rules allow every person in my family to enter, so I'm thinking of having fun trying to come up with odd ways to pick winners, and let my kids pick their own brackets.So, some obvious ones to start, then I'm opening up for suggestions:How close the team lives to my hometownThe apparent ferocity of the team's mascots.Uniform colors
