Not terribly applicable to this instance, but I remember when I took a stats class in college, the professor mentioned how the Army ran this massive long-term study, where they wanted to see if there was any indicator as to who would develop into great leaders. So they monitored a bunch of different traits in recruits during boot camp, and tracked their career paths. In the end, they tried to correlate the soldiers who became leaders with a specific trait identified in boot camp. The one thing that stood out with a huge correlation: all the natural leaders preferred chocolate pudding.
